               <p>I keep a publick-house in <placeName id="t17800405-20-crimeloc125">Robinhood-court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17800405-20-crimeloc125" type="placeName" value="Robinhood-court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17800405-20-crimeloc125" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17800405-20-off123 t17800405-20-crimeloc125"></join>. On the 22d of March, about five o'clock, the prisoner was going by my house. My wife said she suspected she was going to steal some of our pots. I saw her go into a house opposite where there was a pot standing in the passage. She came out, I laid hold of her and said, she had something which was not her own. She said she had not. I opened her cloak and found this quart pot; and in her apron I found another quart pot and a pint pot. I sent for Mr. Mayor, his name was upon this pot.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178004050036"></xptr>(The pot was produced in court and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>Going by I saw the pot stand, and was going to carry it home.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17800405-20-verdict126" type="verdictDescription">
